---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="A Greenwich, CT based investment manager focused on asset-backed lending and specialty finance.">

<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="page-hero-breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> / About</p>
    <h1>Our <strong>Story</strong></h1>
    <p class="page-hero-sub">A Greenwich, CT based investment manager focused on asset-backed lending and specialty finance.</p>
    <div class="page-hero-rule"></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="page-tabs" role="tablist">
      <button class="page-tab is-active" role="tab" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="panel-firm" id="tab-firm">Our Firm</button>
      <button class="page-tab" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="panel-team" id="tab-team">Leadership Team</button>
    </div>

    <div class="tab-panel is-active" id="panel-firm" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-firm">

      <div class="who-grid fade-in">
        <div>
          <div class="section-header">
            <p class="section-label">About Monachil</p>
            <h2 class="section-title">Rooted in <strong>risk management</strong></h2>
          </div>
          <div class="who-text">
            <p>Monachil Capital Partners is a Greenwich, CT based investment manager focused on <strong>asset-backed lending and specialty finance</strong> with a {site.yearsTrackRecord}+ year track record. We directly originate privately negotiated, senior-secured investments, with the intent of providing investors with downside-protected yield and consistent current income.</p>
            <p>We differentiate ourselves with our <strong>data-driven approach</strong>, where we monitor and reconcile collateral in near real time, and partner with high-growth originators seeking capital solutions.</p>
            <p>The firm strives to underwrite with a <strong>capital preservation-first mandate</strong> on all investments with downside protection, control, and transparency as the foundation. Prioritizing diversity of investments by industry, product and geography, strict covenants, data analytics, and sizing deals in the $5&ndash;30mm range helps drive performance and mitigate risk.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pillars">
          <div class="pillar">
            <div class="pillar-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg></div>
            <div>
              <p class="pillar-title">Capital Preservation First</p>
              <p class="pillar-desc">Every investment is underwritten with capital preservation as the primary objective, with structural protections to preserve principal.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar">
            <div class="pillar-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="18" y1="20" x2="18" y2="10"/><line x1="12" y1="20" x2="12" y2="4"/><line x1="6" y1="20" x2="6" y2="14"/></svg></div>
            <div>
              <p class="pillar-title">Proprietary Risk Platform</p>
              <p class="pillar-desc">Consumes source data, reconciles portfolio-level information, and provides daily asset performance reporting.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar">
            <div class="pillar-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/></svg></div>
            <div>
              <p class="pillar-title">LP Alignment</p>
              <p class="pillar-desc">Senior management has significant personal capital invested alongside LPs, ensuring alignment of interests.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar">
            <div class="pillar-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="23 4 23 10 17 10"/><polyline points="1 20 1 14 7 14"/><path d="M3.51 9a9 9 0 0 1 14.85-3.36L23 10M1 14l4.64 4.36A9 9 0 0 0 20.49 15"/></svg></div>
            <div>
              <p class="pillar-title">Disciplined & Repeatable</p>
              <p class="pillar-desc">Process-driven alpha through a transparent, disciplined framework proven across market cycles.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="responsible-investing fade-in">
        <p class="section-label">Responsible Investing</p>
        <p>Monachil integrates responsible investing considerations into its underwriting process, evaluating originator practices, borrower treatment standards, and portfolio impact alongside traditional credit analysis.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="section section--alt fade-in">
        <div class="section-header section-header--centered">
          <p class="section-label">Our Journey</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">Firm <strong>Milestones</strong></h2>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline">
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-year">2019</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <h4 class="timeline-title">Firm Founded</h4>
              <p class="timeline-desc">Ali Meli founds Monachil Capital Partners in Greenwich, CT, drawing on nearly 15 years at Goldman Sachs.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-year">2019</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <h4 class="timeline-title">First Loan Originated</h4>
              <p class="timeline-desc">Monachil closes its inaugural privately negotiated, senior-secured asset-backed investment.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-year">2020</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <h4 class="timeline-title">First Fund Launched</h4>
              <p class="timeline-desc">Launch of first commingled fund vehicle, establishing the firm's flagship private credit strategy.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-year">2022</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <h4 class="timeline-title">MCIF Launch</h4>
              <p class="timeline-desc">Monachil Credit Income Fund, a registered interval fund, launches to broaden investor access to the strategy.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-year">2023</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <h4 class="timeline-title">Growing Media Presence</h4>
              <p class="timeline-desc">Ali Meli becomes a regular guest on Bloomberg, CNBC, and Schwab Network, sharing market insights.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-year">2025</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <h4 class="timeline-title">Continued Growth</h4>
              <p class="timeline-desc">Platform expansion with deepened origination channels and proprietary data analytics capabilities.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="stats fade-in">
        <div class="stats-grid">
          <div>
            <p class="stat-number">2019</p>
            <p class="stat-label">Founded</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="stat-number">$5–30M</p>
            <p class="stat-label">Typical Deal Size</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="stat-number">$30M+</p>
            <p class="stat-label">Senior Management Capital Committed</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="stat-number">2</p>
            <p class="stat-label">Investment Vehicles</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="tab-panel" id="panel-team" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-team">

      <div class="section-header fade-in">
        <p class="section-label">Leadership</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Executive <strong>Team</strong></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="team-member fade-in">
        <div class="team-photo">
          <img src="/images/headshot02.jpg" alt="Ali Meli — Founder & CIO, Monachil Capital Partners" width="400" height="527" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="team-name">Ali Meli</h3>
          <p class="team-title-role">Founder & Chief Investment Officer</p>
          <div class="team-bio">
            <p>The investment platform was founded by Ali Meli in 2019, rooted in a strong risk management ethos and processes attributed to his <strong>nearly 15 years working at Goldman Sachs</strong> as a Partner and Global Co-Head of the Structured Finance, Investing and Lending group.</p>
            <p>This group was one of the most profitable business units at the firm with Ali at the helm, having most notably <strong>engineered the "tactical short" on the housing market</strong> prior to the 2008 market collapse.</p>
            <p>Through the 2010s, Ali was at the forefront of financing the first wave of fintech and consumer finance originators, developing early insight into the outsized returns available from partnering with high-growth lenders in need of capital. It is this experience — understanding both the risks and the opportunity in backing emerging originators — that became the inspiration for <strong>Monachil's investment strategy</strong>.</p>
            <p>Ali holds a B.S. in Electrical Engineering and Management Science from the <strong>Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT)</strong>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="team-member fade-in">
        <div class="team-photo">
          <img src="/images/headshot01.jpg" alt="Joseph McNeila — Senior Advisor, Monachil Capital Partners" width="400" height="640" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="team-name">Joseph McNeila</h3>
          <p class="team-title-role">Senior Advisor</p>
          <div class="team-bio">
            <p>Joseph McNeila serves as Senior Advisor to Monachil Capital Partners, providing strategic and operational guidance to management. He previously served as President and CFO of the firm (2021&ndash;2025).</p>
            <p>Prior to Monachil, McNeila spent <strong>18 years at Goldman Sachs</strong> in New York and London, where he founded the Principal Funding and Investments group in New York and established and ran the European branch for 10 years, developing the Structured Lending platform.</p>
            <p>Earlier in his career, McNeila was a CPA and auditor at Ernst & Young. He holds a BBA in Accountancy from Baruch College and an MBA in Finance from Columbia University.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="team-summary fade-in">
        <p>Monachil's team comprises <strong>nearly 20 professionals across five countries</strong>, spanning investments, business development, technology, and fund operations.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt fade-in">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header section-header--centered">
      <h2 class="section-title">Interested in <strong>working with us</strong>?</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle mx-auto">We welcome conversations with investors and partners who share our commitment to disciplined, data-driven investing.</p>
      <div class="section-cta">
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn--primary">Contact Us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
